protein_properties.bio:functionText: FUNCTION: Growth factor of the TGF-beta superfamily that plays essential roles in many developmental processes, including cardiogenesis, neurogenesis, and osteogenesis (PubMed:18436533, PubMed:24362451, PubMed:31019025). Induces cartilage and bone formation (PubMed:3201241). Initiates the canonical BMP signaling cascade by associating with type I receptor BMPR1A and type II receptor BMPR2 (PubMed:15064755, PubMed:17295905, PubMed:18436533). bio:proteinName: Membrane progestin receptor delta (mPR delta) (Membrane progesterone P4 receptor delta) (Membrane progesterone receptor delta) (Progesterone and adipoQ receptor family member 6) (Progestin and adipoQ receptor family member 6)
protein_properties.bio:functionText: FUNCTION: Plasma membrane progesterone (P4) receptor coupled to G proteins (PubMed:23161870, PubMed:23763432). Seems to act through a G(s) mediated pathway (PubMed:23161870). Involved in neurosteroid inhibition of apoptosis (PubMed:23161870). May be involved in regulating rapid P4 signaling in the nervous system (PubMed:23763432). Also binds dehydroepiandrosterone (DHEA), pregnanolone, pregnenolone and allopregnanolone (PubMed:23161870, PubMed:23763432). {ECO:0000269|PubMed:23161870, ECO:0000303

FUNCTION: E3 ubiquitin ligase essential for DNA replication origin activation during S phase (PubMed:31160578). Acts as a replication origin selector which selects the origins to be fired and catalyzes the multi-mono-ubiquitination of a subset of chromatin-bound ORC3 and ORC5 during S-phase (PubMed:31160578). {ECO:0000269|PubMed:31160578}.
